  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6998.99 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (18.6B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level as they hedge their long gamma positions. The PIN regime and thick positive gamma concentration from 7000-7100 creates a strong magnetic pull toward mean reversion, with dealers providing natural resistance on rallies and support on dips above the 6875 flip line. Watch 7000 as the critical inflection point - any break above faces immediate dealer selling pressure, while a rejection here should see support build toward 6875 where the gamma profile flips negative.\n\nBottom line: expect SPX to get capped hard at 7000 with downside bias toward 6900-6875.",
